This paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves refining feature representations, which is a technique used in many AI applications (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of neural networks to attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the method proposed in the paper involves transforming the input data, which is a technique used in many neural network architectures (cs.NE).
